<div>Hello,<br>
<br>
Thank you for contacting AWS Premium Support, it was a pleasure assisting y=
ou via chime regarding the issue you observed for pushing images. Please se=
e recap below:<br>
<br>
<br>
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D<br>
Issue<br>
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D<br>
Using command from this doc[1] you observed images not pushing as expected =
along with &quot;command not found&quot; errors for skopeo. You worked with=
 our Linux team however you still encountered issues with skopeo at which p=
oint I joined the call to assist with clarification
 and an alternative solutions<br>
<br>
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D<br>
Clarifications<br>
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D<br>
After joining the call I clarified that the commands provided here[1] regar=
ding skopeo and copying images from the public source ecr repo to a target =
repo were simply template commands. The commands should instead be updated =
with the correct image &amp; tag along
 with a real target repo / registry. However due to failure to use skopeo I=
 showed you the alternative docker and ecr commands.<br>
<br>
<br>
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D<br>
Actions Taken<br>
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D<br>
1. The first step in the process I had you take was creating an ECR repo[2]=
 in order to host the images in which you required and needed to push to a =
target repo to use for your EKS pods.<br>
2. After the repo was successfully created I walked you through the process=
[3] of pulling down the public ecr images, tagging them, and pushing them t=
o the newly created ecr repo. I have provided the commands and images below=
:<br>
<br>
<br>
