<br>
3. After successfully pulling down the required images, tagging them, and p=
ushing them to your repo as expected I walked you through updating the exis=
ting dynatrace resources in the EKS Cluster to use the new images pushed to=
 the repo. I have provided the example
 yaml template file here[4] to reflect where the images need to be inserted=
 into your dynakube yaml manifest:<br>
<br>
3a. Navigate to the image and replace the image with the corresponding onea=
gent image: 991497151145.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/dynatrace:1.311.91=
.20251105-194141-1<br>
<br>
kubectl edit ds &lt;dynatrace-ds-name&gt; -n dynatrace<br>
kubectl rollout restart ds &lt;dynatrace-ds-name&gt; -n dynatrace<br>
<br>
3b. Navigate to &quot;activegate&quot; section in the yaml file to add &quo=
t;image&quot; and insert the activegate image: 991497151145.dkr.ecr.us-east=
-1.amazonaws.com/dynatrace:1.325.27.20251027-143735<br>
<br>
vi dynakube.yaml<br>
kubectl delete sts &lt;dynatrace-sts-name&gt; -n dynatrace<br>
<br>
3c. I have also provided our public ecr repo for dynatrace here[5] for futu=
re reference to retrieve any other images you may need to pull down in the =
